<dl id="n06157p"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06157p">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06157p"> 157(p)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> be in charity with</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[from THE SACRAMENT OF THE LORD&apos;S SUPPER]</font> <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> &ldquo;<mark>IN CHARITY WITH</mark> ALL MEN.&rdquo;&mdash;Love. The greatest of all Christian graces is charity. The new commandment is &ldquo;That ye love one another.&rdquo; The divine precept is &ldquo;Love your enemies.&rdquo; <small> Anonymous, <a name="ATCC" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ATCC"><cite title="source">Analysis of the Church Catechism</cite></a> (1879) 57</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
